// ── Live-mode technique samples: Étouffé ──
// Self-recorded on Yijun's harp (CC0), tuned to A=440. Étouffé: plucked and
// immediately hand-damped — a muted attack with a short ring. Each recording
// is cut just before the audible damp contact (the app's damp DSP supplies
// the ending: uniformly at ETOUF_RING for a lone note, instantly on
// force-damp), so rings run ~0.17–0.39 s (bass wires longest), plus 50 ms of
// trailing silence so the decoded buffer never ends at the file edge (no
// end-of-note click). Fades are applied after afftdn, which truncates ~29 ms
// from its output end. Keys are the *sounding* MIDI at A=440 with the
// measured residual folded in (float) so playbackRate lands the note on
// pitch; 7Eb is keyed to nominal MIDI (tuner-verified in tune — low wires
// read sharp at the attack, then settle). Same shape as HARMONIC_SAMPLES.
export const ETOUFFE_SAMPLES = {};
